additional information properties of the norm \(\|v\| = 0\) IFF \(v=0\) \(\|\lambda v\| = |\lambda|\|v\|\) Proof:
By definition of an inner product, \(\langle v,v \rangle = 0\) only when \(v=0\) See algebra: \begin{align} \|\lambda v\|^{2} &amp;= \langle \lambda v, \lambda v \rangle \\ &amp;= \lambda \langle v, \lambda v \rangle \\ &amp;= \lambda \bar{\lambda} \langle v,v \rangle \\ &amp;= |\lambda |^{2} \|v\|^{2} \end{align}

